      "content": "it's not just a hacker though, hackers don't act this... continuous. it's like a living thing. every time i try to log in or fix something, the posts just change to match what i'm doing, almost like it's reacting to me in real time. it feels like the \"me\" that exists on the internet isn't me anymore, it's this digital version that's actually more active than i am. can an AI actually become a permanent replacement for a person? like, if it carries on my life better than I do, am I even real anymore?",
